message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Agent Deployment into Coupled Systems: A Working Framework"
version: "1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-30"
authors:
  - family-names: "Alioto"
    given-names: "John P."
abstract: >
  A structural framework for analyzing the deployment of AI agents into
  coupled operational systems. Identifies the primitive that AI agents are
  built around, the composition path from primitive to autonomous system,
  the deployment error that produces the central failure mode (false
  closure), and the dynamics that govern how that failure propagates
  through coupled engineered systems. Intended for engineers, architects,
  operators, and governance practitioners working on agent deployment.
keywords:
  - AI agents
  - agent deployment
  - LLM agents
  - coupled systems
  - cascade dynamics
  - operational closure
  - false closure
  - viability theory
  - resilience engineering
  - AI safety
type: report
url: "https://github.com/jpalioto/agent-lifecycle-framework"
license-url: "https://github.com/jpalioto/agent-lifecycle-framework"
